		"npnf",
		"schaff"
	],
	"prologue": {
		"body": {
			"en-US": "From the *Didache* and St. Clement of Rome at the close of the apostolic age to St. John of Damascus eight centuries later, these are the writers whose words carried the faith from the upper room to the cathedrals of Christendom. The English translations gathered here are the great Victorian editions — the **Ante-Nicene Fathers** (Edinburgh, 1885–1896, Alexander Roberts and James Donaldson) and the **Nicene and Post-Nicene Fathers** (New York, 1886–1900, Philip Schaff and Henry Wace), 38 volumes between them — long out of copyright, revised and put online by Kevin Knight for New Advent, and now imported here as 419 individual works."
		}
	},
